<Author>batboy_nl
<Content>Great bargain central hotel Stayed at this hotel for a week (august- september 2008) having found it through a booking website at 60 euro per night for an ensuite double. was amazed to find something so cheap in the centre and to be honest its more a 1 plus or 2 minus than just a 1 star.Read all of the reviews prior to going and was expecting something awful - was worried about the size of room, the safe, the rude staff, the cleanliness etc etc but found none of them a problem. Size of room was not really an issue - with city centre hotel at that price you expect compact and it was bigger than we expected - ensuite and room were big enough for two people to move around and get ready etc with no problem. it wasnt like we spent hours in the room other than sleeping so not a problem.the safe we didnt use because of the warning on here but it looked like the standard model used in all the hotels where i've never had a problemthe staff worried me - even though we always treat staff well and dont expect the usual problems, we are a gay couple and the reports on the old guy here and others worried me - but they were all fabulous. They treated us with respect and smiles (the latter normally missing in spain :-)). the so called rude old guy chatted and joked with us a couple of times as well and so did the middle aged guy so i really cant see why other people have had problems - of course we did the usual things anyone would do lik elearning to say hello goodbye please and thank you in catalan rather than using english or spanish and i think that helped.in terms of cleanliness i cant see what the fuss was about - very clean with bedding and towels totally changed every day we were there. sure some of the fixtures and fittings were a bit dated but no prob we didnt have trouble with noise other than one morning when 2 of the cleaners woke us up (1030am so not too early) with a loud conversation and the electrical sockets are a problem in their number and location - one at ceiling height for a non existent tv and one in the bathroom - we had to improvise a shelf for our travel kettle but that was no prob - next time i go i'll take an extension leadOverall i would recommend this to other travellers and indeed already have. Next time we go we will use the same place without hesitation. Its very convenient for Liceu metro and the Ramblas Jaume metro and the cathedral. there are some great bars and restaurants within a 10 minute radius and its now added to my list of good clean value for money european city break hotels.I would also really really recommend it for gay travellers on a budget - rather than paying more for the hotels who advertise as gay friendly and charge for it, pick this one where the staff treat everyone with the same level of respect and friendliness as the guests give them . 
