<Author>Nurse51brigg
<Content>Ideal central location. Like many other reviewers, read the reviews AFTER a friend booked it for us.We were very apprehensive.I printed out a map of the hotel's location and arranged our journey from Estacio du Nord (The bus station near Arc de Triomf metro.) by metro (Taxi is reasonable if you can find one that is free)We travelled to Jaume metro. Found the street leading to the Plaka Jaume and the very narrow street to the hotel very easily. (about 2030 at night)I think every spare blank wall in Barcelona has grafitti on it.Which is very sad. Major towns in England are the same.LIke most of the previous reviews my comments would match, rooms clean, beds, changed every day, clean towels, HOT water all the time. Toilet clean.The three men that manned the desk, were always helpful.I speak a little spanish so that went a long way. BUT even if you dont , shouldnt be a problem.Our room was on the third floor near the lift, which we rareley heard. Our small window faced a wall. NOt a problem as it made the room very peaceful and you wouldnt know you were in a very vibrant bustling city. Like a previous reviewer didnt know what the weather was like until we ventured out.I feel sorry for the 2004 person who had there safe robbed, but we had no problems. Its a coded safe, and you just have to remember your code.Warned about pickpockets etc, but you use your noddle, take a bun bag or a zipped bag., and place it in front of you.THe downsides we experienced were, there are NO plug points in the room ( we took a kettle and couldnt use it.) MIssed my early morning cuppa.I couldnt charge up my mobile phone either.The other ,was a fellow English guest waking the whole of the hotel cos he couldnt get into his room. Everyone I think in Barcelona knew his wifes name by the time he finished. Unfortunate for us on our 1st night. He left the same morning .I hasten to add the following 4 nights were peaceful.THe hotel is a few minutes walk from the Ramblas and Liceu Metro. where there are Lots of eating places all competing for customers, cheap and otherwise. So you pays your money and takes your choice.Every morning the streets surrounding the hotel are washed and hosed down. Rubbish is removed every night or early morning.Lots of major tourist sites of easy walking distance from the hotel.Small cafe round the corner for a nice cup of Cafe con Leche ot Te con Leche and snacks for breakfast.Metro multi ticket very cheap and covers a large area.Watch the days and times of opening of the sites you want to see.If you have booked a short stay you may miss an attraction you want to see because its not open the days you have booked. IE the Magic fountain at Mont Juic which is only on Thurs, FRi Sat and Sun.I would stay at this hotel again. 
