<Content>A comfortable stay at the Call I stayed at the Hotel Call from 7th-12th February 2004. The room was very clean (as was the hotel as a whole in fact) with a bed, toilet, shower, safe and telephone. Quite basic, but as this was all I needed it was ideal for the price.The lack of a proper window was quite weird, as I didn?t know what the weather was like each day until I got outside. Apparently, all single rooms in the Hotel Call are like this. Instead there was an interior window that opened out onto a shaft which led up to the roof. This may be useful for some cool air in the summer, although the air conditioning did its job fine in February!The hotel was surprisingly noisy. I couldn?t here any noise from the streets, but I could clearly hear lots of noise from the floor that I was on, e.g. people talking, footsteps and doors closing. It seemed like the walls were paper-thin.The Hotel is in the middle of the Barri Gotic area, a perfect location for the bars, cafes, restaurants, shops and historic buildings in that area, although the streets around there are quite dark and narrow.Benito and his staff were very friendly and spoke good English. There was someone at reception 24 hours a day, which was useful when I got back late at night.Barcelona is a fantastic city. If you get the chance, go, and if you?re travelling on a budget and don?t need the luxuries that other hotels will charge you extra for, I recommend the Hotel Call. 
