<Content>Call in at the 'Call' for an accessable stay in Barcelona We booked this hotel because it was one of the only places that we could book due to it being Colombus weekend, and everywhere we loked at was full. The hotel is situated up a small side street amongst a labyrinth of small, charming little streets behind the Gothic Cathedral. The hotel rooms are pleasantly decorated, and comfortable, many have a window which overlooks the street, which isn't noisy late at night. The bathroom was fine, the shower had consistantly hot water which was a bonus. There's nothing worse than running out of hot water! The sheets were changed daily which was good, and the room kept neat and tidy. There is a safe in the hotel room. This was easy to use, and an extra we found very beneficial. Barcelona has a lot of beggars and pick pockets, so it's a good idea to take enough cash out for the day and leave the rest safely put away. There is a neon hotel sign which is a great help late at night wondering round the streets trying to find it!! Make sure you get a landmark close by to head for because all the streets look the same in the early hours! It's about a 6 min walk from Liceu station, and is in a great position to get to most of the centrally situated museums, churches and other places of interest. Restaurants, bars, discos and bustling squares for eating whilst people watching are within a few minutes walk, as is the Ramblas. There is a 24hour receptionist who is friendly enough, but looks slightly startled at being woken at 5am!! A good place to stay, reasonably priced (we paid 拢22 each for a twin room)and a place I would reccommend to friends who were visiting the city, and somewhere I would go back to on my next visit. 
